OL,3,C70th anniversary of ITV being
OL,4,Ccelebrated on regional news programmes
OL,6,FIt went on the air in 1958 while much
OL,7,Fof the rest of Wales had to wait until
OL,8,F1962 and the launch of the doomed
OL,9,FTeledu Cymru. Then came Harlech in
OL,10,F1968 and the start of the direct
OL,11,Flineage which leads to modern ITV.
OL,13,FOther parts of Wales though got ITV in
OL,14,F1956 when the Midlands and Lancashire
OL,15,Ftransmitters opened. This was not
OL,16,Fconsidered overspill reception at the
OL,17,Ftime.
OL,19,FSimilar points could be made in many
OL,20,Fother regions.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/8
